l-NIR wavelengths remains approximately constant over 35 Myr, for\nsimulations with and without AGN winds. In the case without winds, this occurs\ndespite the rapid compaction, and is due to heavy dust obscuration in the inner\nregions of the galaxy. This work highlights the importance of forward-modelling\nwhen comparing simulated and observed galaxy populations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 22 Mar 2023 18:40:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 17 May 2023 14:03:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-31"}
